Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.54,0:00:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.50,0:00:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean\Nby "it's over", Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It means the investigation\NI hired you for is now over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.64,0:00:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.51,0:00:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that the investigation\Non Karl Neuman is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.39,0:00:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He was your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.19,0:00:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank you for your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.34,0:00:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute, that doesn't mean\Nthat the matter is settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.78,0:00:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still possible that Edmond Fahren's\Ndeath was not a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.49,0:00:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We also don't know the identity of the\Nperson who was behind Fahren either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has been settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.59,0:00:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The tea is ready, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.55,0:00:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.38,0:00:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.47,0:01:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm fine, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.31,0:01:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you for your work.\NPlease send us your bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice weather outside, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.07,0:01:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.61,0:01:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.11,0:01:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? Johan is here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.50,0:01:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that icy man, who's never trusted\Nanyone or let anyone get close, become\Nsuch a softy because of his son?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.59,0:01:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.55,0:01:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe that's the same man that\Nwas called "the Vampire of Bayern."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.43,0:01:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"Is that so? Johan is here, too?", huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.49,0:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're currently trying to\Nfind this puppy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:27.93,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(625,500)\pos(360,340)}Just One Case
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.87,0:03:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that my client's ex-husband\Ntook it away after the divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.71,0:03:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a difficult situation...\Na custody battle over a puppy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.97,0:03:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but I'll be having some wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.14,0:03:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.31,0:03:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay with just water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.10,0:03:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you say that you're\Nfree from your job,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't seem like you're\Ninterested in drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.98,0:03:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I'm fine in that respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.86,0:04:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"In that respect"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.45,0:04:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something else that\Nyou're worried about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.70,0:04:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because I've got some free time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.45,0:04:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing some silly things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been flipping though a scrapbook I made when\NI was a detective. It's full of all my unsolved cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.42,0:04:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you look at that, what do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Frustrated...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That homicide, this homicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.02,0:04:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think about how the perpetrators\Nare living comfortably outside of prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.35,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't take it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.90,0:04:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel frustrated at my lack of ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.28,0:04:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You had the ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.19,0:04:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard, you tried so hard and became\Ntoo attached to your cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.53,0:04:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You became frustrated at your inability\Nto read the perpetrator's mind and...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I turned to alcohol...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.33,0:04:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to have kept you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.59,0:04:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the food's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.55,0:05:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't necessarily think\Nthat that's a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.97,0:05:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the fact that you're flipping through\Nyour scrapbook of past cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.93,0:05:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just get frustrated again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.56,0:05:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you should be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.27,0:05:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to tell me what you think of\Nthe cases when you look over them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You got drunk and killed that young\Nboy who was a serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.70,0:05:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You are now prepared to face\Nthat fact head on,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,yet you're still trying not to remember what went\Nthrough your mind when you pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.51,0:05:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You still see that young boy's\Nghost, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.80,0:05:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.89,0:05:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When everything is clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.68,0:05:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and when it comes into broad daylight,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that ghost will go away too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.89,0:06:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When everything comes into\Nbroad daylight, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.02,0:06:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The homicide of Holmar the accountant...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.86,0:06:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim, Joakim Holmar, had been\Nsteadily building up his career.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't the type of person\Nwho people would resent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.41,0:06:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no indication that\Nit was a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.95,0:06:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Voice of God" homicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.41,0:06:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims were an\Nex-housekeeper and a driver...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:07:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At both crime scenes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a mysterious message proclaiming that the killer had\Nheard the voice of God was written on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.18,0:07:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The homicide of the Dornah Company CEO...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.97,0:07:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the leading investigators in Bayern, Ruto Gakushi, was found dead in the Hartoholtz forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.23,0:07:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Spiras homicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.82,0:07:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A middle-aged couple drowned and was\Nfound upstream in the Izar River.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.45,0:07:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The case was grouped with the serial\Nhomicides of middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The primary suspect, a Japanese doctor, is still on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.46,0:07:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I started drinking more as the number\Nof unsolved cases rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, things are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.43,0:07:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.97,0:07:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like the doctor said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.10,0:07:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what it's like to think while sober...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.69,0:08:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.40,0:08:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.15,0:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.31,0:08:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you thinking about at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.56,0:08:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.11,0:08:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about something but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.74,0:08:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Your flash of insight disappeared when\Nyou saw that young boy's ghost?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.49,0:08:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.24,0:08:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be impatient.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your flash of insight will\Ncome back to you someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What was my realization?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.76,0:09:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt as though it was an important key\Nto solving one of those unsolved cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.27,0:09:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Must have been my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.32,0:09:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.39,0:09:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.66,0:09:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's following me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.42,0:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like that one time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.80,0:09:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That time, I was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.84,0:09:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also running through this hallway...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.59,0:09:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Chasing him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.57,0:10:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for bothering you this\Nlate at night, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.74,0:10:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. It seems like you finally feel\Nlike telling me the entire story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.37,0:10:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll listen to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.91,0:10:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That time, I saw it in the young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that it did exist in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.09,0:10:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that true evil existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.63,0:10:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.13,0:10:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,shot the young boy dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.76,0:10:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Good job telling me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.31,0:10:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You've finally been able to\Nget back on your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.06,0:10:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.52,0:10:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.36,0:10:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That flash of insight I had...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.32,0:10:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the many unsolved\Ncases that bothered me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.20,0:10:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.78,0:10:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.06,0:11:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Dr. Gillen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.57,0:11:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the pleasure of reading your\Nwork that you sent to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.90,0:11:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"A Summary of\NTranscendental Criminal Psychology."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.82,0:11:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pleased that one of my students...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.74,0:11:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,from my days of teaching at the\NUniversity of DÃ¼sseldorf...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.54,0:11:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is having such success.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.77,0:11:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Dr. Gillen,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.09,0:11:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you told me before that during your interview\Nwith the serial killer Peter Jurgens,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.60,0:11:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he told you that he'd committed the murders\Nbecause one of his friends had ordered him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.81,0:11:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since my memory isn't certain,\Ncould you tell me again...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.53,0:11:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what the name of Jurgen's friend was...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.33,0:12:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,P.S. You were a very good student in college,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.75,0:12:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but there was another who could compete\Nwith you for the top rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.67,0:12:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He chose the path of neurosurgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.68,0:12:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but he is now the primary suspect\Nin a serial homicide case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.81,0:12:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you know anything about him,\Nplease let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.73,0:12:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of man was he,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.52,0:12:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and where is he now...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.61,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The man called Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.99,0:12:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're that detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.91,0:12:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm just a private investigator\Nwho barely scrapes by.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.41,0:12:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for bringing up a hard subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.92,0:12:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but may I ask you questions regarding\Nthe "Voice of God" homicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in which your mother was a victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.38,0:12:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.92,0:12:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,After four years, the police no longer\Nput any effort into the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.18,0:13:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.56,0:13:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, your mother\Nwas a housekeeper, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.94,0:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but that was over 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the reason that she\Nstopped working for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.45,0:13:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Her health had declined,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.24,0:13:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so she stuck to working\Naround the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be possible that she didn't\Nget along with Mr. Schuwald?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.96,0:13:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No! On the contrary,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother loved poetry, and while Mr.\NSchuwald could still see, she and he...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.17,0:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,used to read poetry to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.39,0:13:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.93,0:13:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.98,0:13:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've kept these through the years because\Nmother thought much of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.15,0:13:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All these poetry books were presents\Nfrom Mr. Schuwald to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.66,0:14:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would have thought that the detective who\Ninvestigated the Dornah CEO homicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.70,0:14:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,would now be a private investigator...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.60,0:14:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As the CEO's secretary, I'd like to\Nask you some questions again...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding the people who hated the CEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.85,0:14:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The CEO's enemies?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you before that there was\Nan endless number of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.15,0:14:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The police should have finished the analysis\Nof the list of companies that went\Nbankrupt because of CEO Gauk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.77,0:14:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There is another notable\Ninvestigator in Bayern, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.55,0:14:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his relationship with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.76,0:14:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about Mr. Schuwald, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those two were lifelong rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.53,0:14:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.49,0:14:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Schuwald went bankrupt twice in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.12,0:14:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,His second bankruptcy was a direct result\Nof fierce competition with CEO Gauk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.24,0:15:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Schuwald was\Ncrushed because of the CEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.30,0:15:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But the CEO had also been\Nhit by Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They hated each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.18,0:15:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.84,0:15:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever they met at a party, there\Nwould always be a big ruckus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They would argue passionately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.69,0:15:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two would?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, those two cold people would.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.70,0:15:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were the only ones who could\Nargue with each other on par.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than being rivals,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.04,0:15:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They were actually friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.80,0:15:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Watch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Hans? I knew him well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.45,0:16:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He was one of the two victims in\Nthe "Voice of God" homicides.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.58,0:16:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too bad. He was a good guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.29,0:16:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Mr. Hans really such a good person?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.67,0:16:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he would often buy me drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.72,0:16:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He was Mr. Schuwald's driver, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.43,0:16:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.56,0:16:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was over 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.10,0:16:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why he was fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.61,0:16:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because Mr. Schuwald went\Nbankrupt around then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.11,0:16:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.57,0:16:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't because of any trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.66,0:16:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.66,0:16:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you this to defend Hans's honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.37,0:16:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a good guy who could\Nget along with everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.54,0:16:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,be they rich people or poor people like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.50,0:17:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He used to often say...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.09,0:17:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that he taught the rich guy\Nhow to enjoy bird watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.47,0:17:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Bird watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.30,0:17:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he said that when he\Ntook him to the forests,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.72,0:17:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that vampire would be as happy as a little kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already been two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.69,0:17:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but I still remember my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.86,0:17:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was a very serious man,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.32,0:17:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one had any real\Nreason to dislike him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.66,0:17:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I still can't believe someone would\Nwant to murder him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.95,0:17:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My sympathies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.20,0:17:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me, but your husband was a...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.27,0:17:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent his childhood in an orphanage...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.42,0:17:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and lived with several foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.96,0:17:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After much difficulty,\Nhe became an accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.76,0:17:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your husband was asked by Mr. Schuwald\Nto be his personal accountant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.05,0:17:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.89,0:17:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He refused him every time, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.27,0:17:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the fact that he was busy\Nwith what was then his job,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.90,0:18:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but he said that their philosophies\Non money were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband was very strict\Nwith money, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.32,0:18:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.91,0:18:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think the perpetrator\Nwill be caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.95,0:18:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll work hard on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.37,0:18:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He will definitely be caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.12,0:18:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.92,0:18:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.00,0:18:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how your husband\Nand Mr. Schuwald met?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.09,0:18:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he said they met in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.26,0:18:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.05,0:18:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was back when Mr. Schuwald could still see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.18,0:18:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They happened to run across\Neach other in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.00,0:18:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why in a place like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They were bird watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.52,0:18:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, he would go with\NMr. Schuwald many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.91,0:18:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Bird watching...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.04,0:18:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy like a kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.04,0:19:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Read poetry to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.75,0:19:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.14,0:19:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.01,0:19:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I'm fine. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.81,0:19:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What a horrible driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.98,0:19:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rather, it seemed as though\Nhe was targeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.40,0:19:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.74,0:19:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done my research.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.12,0:19:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just like I told you the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.99,0:19:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The unsolved cases that bothered\Nme when I was a detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.95,0:19:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,were all pointing in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.34,0:19:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Voice of God" homicides,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.59,0:19:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the Dornah CEO homicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.34,0:19:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the accountant homicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.89,0:19:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At first glance, they seem totally unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.06,0:19:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The modus operandi of each murder\Nwas completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.60,0:20:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The victims were not related to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.10,0:20:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, there was no cash flow\Nlinking them to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.27,0:20:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Their connections did not go\Ninto the records at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, they were all connected\Nby one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.07,0:20:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.95,0:20:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,were committed to isolate Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.62,0:20:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, there's another curious common point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.67,0:20:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Dornah CEO homicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,CEO Gauk left right before the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that he had an important meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.30,0:20:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the person he went to see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the "God" that was written on\Nthe wall in the "Voice of God" homicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.70,0:20:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the only one of my cases\Nthat seemed unrelated,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.81,0:20:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the serial murder of the middle-aged couples in\Nwhich the prime suspect was that Japanese doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.03,0:20:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the name that he mentioned\Nduring his interrogation...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.86,0:20:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the names are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.49,0:20:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Johan."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.91,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A former student of mine,\Na criminal psychologist,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.37,0:21:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,researched a killer who murdered\Nbecause a friend ordered him to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me by mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.63,0:21:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of the friend was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.84,0:21:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.43,0:21:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a common name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.68,0:21:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The connection between the cases\Ncould just be coincidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.94,0:21:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if this were true,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.73,0:21:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then it means that someone named Johan\Nhas committed these murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.78,0:21:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in the span of four years to\Ncompletely isolate Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.99,0:21:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And the prostitute,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.79,0:21:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer, who gave birth to Mr. Schuwald's\Nson, also conveniently died.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.75,0:21:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Fahren, the student who claimed\Nhe was Mr. Schuwald's son...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.79,0:21:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,also conveniently committed suicide\Nonce the real son appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.17,0:21:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If this man, Johan, does exist...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.18,0:21:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.18,0:22:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.27,0:22:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.98,0:22:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.07,0:22:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.71,0:22:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice weather outside, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.03,0:22:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.87,0:22:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right beside Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.11,0:23:53.53,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)\pos(360,340)}Execution
